A company's IAM role has the following policy:

{"Version":"2012-10-17","Statement":[{"Effect":"Allow","Action":"*","Resource":"*","Condition":{"StringEquals":{"aws:RequestedRegion":"us-east-1"}}}]}

A developer using this role tries to describe EC2 instances in eu-west-1 and also calls IAM ListRoles. IAM ListRoles succeeds but EC2 DescribeInstances in eu-west-1 fails. Why does IAM succeed while EC2 fails?
